cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with scene text script identification, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel module for learning a more discriminative representation, which involves machine learning (ML) techniques, making cs.LG a likely sub-category as well. The paper also involves image retrieval (IR) techniques for identifying scripts in images, making cs.IR a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with multi-modal data (text and images), making cs.MM a possible sub-category.
